  "html": "<div class=\"fr-view\"><div class=\"fr-view\"><p><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Week 2 Overview</span></strong></span></p></div><p style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:12.0pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;background:white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>You will learn how to express directions of an action and existence, how to describe something and all hiragana modifiers.</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm;margin-bottom:12.0pt;font-size:16px;font-family:Cambria;margin-top:12.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-left:0cm;background:white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'><strong>Day 6&nbsp;</strong></span></span></span></p></div><ol><li><div class=\"fr-view\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Grammar focus on negative form of past tense Verbs = V-masen deshita (Ｖませんでした)</span></span></span></div></li><li><div class=\"fr-view\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Grammar focus on verbs to go, to come, to go back (ikimas, kimas, kaerimas)</span></span></span></div></li><li><div class=\"fr-view\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Grammar focus on the particle markers for action sentences - he (へ) as the marker of direction of an action, de (で) as the marker of the means of transport, to (と) as a marker of action with someone, and mo (も) used with negative verbs to mean not.</span></span></span></div></li><li><div class=\"fr-view\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Express time in the past (this/last/next year, this/last/next month)&nbsp;</span></span></span></div></li><li><div class=\"fr-view\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Hiragana with voiced syllables (i.e. が, ざ, だ, ば, ぱ)</span></span></span></div></li></ol><div class=\"fr-view\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'><strong>Day 7&nbsp;</strong><br></span></span></span></div><ol><li><div class=\"fr-view\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Grammar focus on the particle itsu (いつ) meaning when (when an action occurs)</span></span></span></div></li><li><div class=\"fr-view\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Grammar focus on the future form&nbsp;</span></span></span></div></li><li><div class=\"fr-view\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Grammar focus on extending an invitation V-masen ka? (Vませんか)</span></span></span></div></li><li><div class=\"fr-view\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Conversation focus - Asking someones age and replying your age (How old are you?)</span></span></span></div></li><li><div class=\"fr-view\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Hiragana with double consonant (small tsu っ)</span></span></span></div></li></ol><div class=\"fr-view\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'><strong>Day 8&nbsp;</strong><br></span></span></span></div><ol><li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Grammar focus on adjectives in positive and negative form</span></span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Grammar focus on the particle soshite (そして) <br></span></span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Grammar focus on the particle ga (が) as a marker to connect ideas that contrast<br></span></span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Express &ldquo;very&rdquo; and &ldquo;not very&rdquo; with totemo (とても) and amari (あまり)<br></span></span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Hiragana with long sounds (かあ, きい, くう, けい, こう)<br></span></span></span></li></ol><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'><strong>Day 9&nbsp;</strong><br></span></span></span></p><ol><li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Grammar focus on how to conjugate an adjective with a noun<br></span></span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Ask &ldquo;what kind of&rdquo;, using the particle donna (どんな)<br></span></span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Ask &ldquo;which one&rdquo; using the expression dore deska (どれですか)<br></span></span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Grammar focus on the particle ne (ね) to express agreement/empathy<br></span></span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Hiragana with contracted sounds (i.e. きゃ、ぎゃ, しゃ, じゃ) <br></span></span></span></li></ol><p><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'><strong>Day 10&nbsp;</strong><br></span></span></span></p><ol><li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Express existence for living and non-living things using the verbs arimas and imas, and the particles ga (が) and ni (に)<br></span></span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Express the number of people staying in a place<br></span></span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif;'>Grammar focus on the particles ya (や), yo (よ), ne (ね)<br></span></span></span></li><li><span style=\"color: rgb(91, 91, 91);\"><span style='font-family:\"Open Sans\", serif; font-size: 16px;'>Hiragana with contracted sounds (i.e. ちゃ, にゃ, ひゃ, びゃ, ぴゃ, みゃ, りゃ)&nbsp;</span></span></li></ol>",
